ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This repository contains an internal IT security audit conducted for a fictional organization, Botium Toys, as part of a cybersecurity portfolio activity.

The objective of this project is to assess the organization's current security posture, identify potential risks and compliance gaps, and provide actionable recommendations using the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (NIST CSF).

Botium Toys is a growing U.S.-based toy company with an expanding online presence and international customers. As the company scales, maintaining regulatory compliance, protecting critical assets, and ensuring business continuity become increasingly important.

ğŸ¯ Audit Objectives

Evaluate the organizationâ€™s security controls and compliance practices.

Identify risks, threats, and vulnerabilities affecting business operations.

Assess alignment with industry standards and regulatory requirements.

Provide recommendations to improve the overall security posture.

Support compliance with online payment processing and EU business regulations.

ğŸ§© Audit Scope

The audit covers:

IT infrastructure and digital assets

Internal security controls

Compliance best practices

Risk assessment based on existing policies and systems

Application of the NIST Cybersecurity Framework

ğŸ› ï¸ Methodology

The audit process followed these steps:

Reviewed audit scope and goals defined by the IT manager.

Identified critical assets managed by the IT department.

Analyzed potential risks and vulnerabilities.

Completed a Controls and Compliance Checklist.

Evaluated alignment with best practices and regulatory expectations.

Performed self-assessment to validate completeness and accuracy.

âœ… Controls and Compliance Checklist

Each control and compliance item was evaluated using a Yes / No assessment.
The checklist includes:

Security controls validation

Compliance best practices verification

Identification of missing or weak controls

Optional recommendations for improvement

